ording to the government of quebec the provincial government plans to offer up to  rebate towards the purchase of an electric car the government hopes that by  a quarter of cars purchased in quebec will be electric the plan would position quebec as a world leader in electrified transportation according to jean charest tata indica ev engine bay featuring tm mфtive electric motor quebec became the first region in north america to set a carbon tax since  consumers pay a special tax on gasoline since july  quebec has imposed a carbon tax that affect more than  of industries in the province this tax will be mandatory from  the sectors affected by this carbon tax will have to reduce their carbon dioxide below   kilotonnes per year only the forest industry agriculture and waste industries are not affected by this tax in addition the quebec government plans to recover  of putrescible organic matter by  in order to reduce its emissions quebec climate policy has been harshly criticised by the federal government under prime minister stephen harper in  former minister jim prentice has openly criticized quebecs plan to set ghg standards for motor vehicles sold in the province describing it as lunatic however ten months later prentice successor john baird has praised quebec as a world leader in ghg abatement most productive sectorsedit aerospaceedit there are some  companies of the aerospace sector that employ  people it includes aerospace companies such as airplane manufacturer bombardier jet engine companies pratt  whitney and rollsroyce canada flight simulator builder cae defence contractor lockheed martin and l communications and helicopter manufacturer bell helicopter  various international organisations have established their headquarters in quebec notably the international air transport association and the international civil aviation organization financeedit the finance insurance real estate and leasing industry employs  people including the largest money manager in canada caisse de dépôt et placement du québec transportationedit quebecs ground transportation industry generated  billion in revenue at the beginning of  it employs some  people and includes major original equipment manufacturers such as bombardier paccar novabus prévost car komatsu international and many suppliers and subcontractors quebec has eight deepwater ports for merchandise shipping and in   million tons of merchandise was carried by  cargo ships through the saint lawrence seaway the income created by this traffic is over  million per annum the port of montreal is the second biggest container handling port in canada located on one of the largest navigable rivers in the world the saint lawrence river it is the third largest port in northeastern north america annual revenues of about  billion are created along with  direct and indirect jobs besides montreal other deepwater ports are located in troisrivières and bécancour as well as in soreltracy baiecomeau portcartier and septîles the last four ports specialise in handling bulk cargo and heavy merchandise information technologyedit this section does not cite any sources please help improve this section by adding citations to reliable sources unsourced material may be challenged and removed february  learn how and when to remove this template message quebecs information technology employed over  workers in  of the total canadian venture capital funding  is managed in quebec with  of available funds invested in technology sectors of note include telecommunications multimedia software computer services and consulting microelectronics and components some  people work for  telecommunication companies such as bell canada ericsson motorola and mitec the multimedia sector was enhanced by electronic arts in  some  people work for game development companies such as ubisoft microïds strategy first am and eidos interactive montreal has two major creators of d animation software softimage and autodesk media and entertainment d