in canada and most public institutions functioned in both languages english was also used in the legislature government commissions and courts since the s languages other than french on commercial signs have been permitted only if french is given marked prominence this law has been the subject of periodic controversy since its inception the written forms of french placenames in canada retain their diacritics such as accent marks over vowels in english text legitimate exceptions are montreal and quebec however the accented forms are increasingly evident in some publications the canadian style states that montréal and québec the city must retain their accents in english federal documents population centres main article list of population centres in quebec largest metropolitan areas in quebec rank core city administrative region pop rank core city administrative region pop view talk edit montreal quebec city gatineau  montreal montréal   rouynnoranda abitibitémiscamingue   quebec city capitalenationale   salaberrydevalleyfield montérégie   gatineau outaouais   saintgeorges chaudièreappalaches   sherbrooke estrie   valdor abitibitémiscamingue   saguenay saguenay–lacsaintjean   alma saguenay–lacsaintjean   troisrivières mauricie   baiecomeau côtenord   saintjeansurrichelieu montérégie   septîles côtenord   drummondville centreduquébec   thetford mines chaudièreappalaches   granby montérégie   rivièreduloup bassaintlaurent   sainthyacinthe montérégie   matane bassaintlaurent   shawinigan mauricie   amos abitibitémiscamingue   rimouski bassaintlaurent   dolbeaumistassini saguenay–lacsaintjean   soreltracy montérégie   la tuque mauricie   joliette lanaudière   lachute laurentides   victoriaville centreduquébec   cowansville montérégie  canada  census economy main article economy of quebec quebec has an advanced marketbased and open economy in  its gross domestic product gdp of us per capita at purchasing power parity puts the province at par with japan italy and spain but r