y was established in quebec due to its major role in this research field a total of three quebecers have been in space since the creation of the csa marc garneau julie payette and guy laliberté quebec has also contributed to the creation of some canadian artificial satellites including scisat isis radarsat and radarsat the province is one of the world leaders in the field of space science and contributed to important discoveries in this field one of the most recent is the discovery of the complex extrasolar planets system hr  hr  is the first direct observation of an exoplanet in history olivier daigle and claude carignan astrophysicists from université de montréal have invented an astronomical camera approximately  times more powerful than those currently on the market it is therefore considered as the most sensitive camera in the world the mont mégantic observatory was recently equipped with this camera quebec ranks among the world leaders in the field of life science william osler wilder penfield donald hebb brenda milner and others made significant discoveries in medicine neuroscience and psychology while working at mcgill university in montreal quebec has more than  biotechnology and pharmaceutical companies which together employ more than  people and  highly qualified researchers montreal is ranked th in north america for the number of jobs in the pharmaceutical sector hubert reeves astrophysicist awarded the albert einstein medal rudolph a marcus chemist and nobel prize in chemistry laureate in  hérouxdevtek has designed and manufactured the undercarriage of apollo lunar module marc garneau the first canadian in outer space october  mont mégantic observatory the second largest telescope in eastern canada a tm mфtive motor invented by tm electrodynamic systems a subsidiary of hydroquébec infrastructure transportation the ferry nm camillemarcoux of the société des traversiers du québec ensuring liaison baiecomeau—matane and godbout—matane development and securi