litythe course of a barrel classification guidelines certifications inventorythe world reserve a record year productionits native land from the forest sustainable development you are apackager industrial importer restaurateur secondary menu about the fpaq contact us media en fr products its native land from the forest maple products classification guidelines certifications health benefits sports nutrition the secret ingredient fact sheets target group packager industrial importer restaurateur its native land the sugar maple tree red or silver holds within it a treasure—maple sap also known as maple water when the freezing temperatures of the québec winter are followed fast by spring’s thaw the precious sap begins to run and it’s collected in québec’s maple forests  pure maple products such as syrup maple butter and maple sugar all come from this single ingredient legend tells of a native north american observing an energetic squirrel drinking the water of a maple tree  was this the actual discovery that led to maple products as we know them today historians have many theories but there is little spoken or written evidence to support any of them one thing is certain the story of maple and its products is inextricably linked to the history of québec  discovery jacques cartier becomes the first european to encounter the maple tree and its sap a native north american tells him that the name for the sugar maple tree is in his language “couton”  “nouvelle cuisine” by exchanging their culinary knowledge europeans and first nations eventually created new ways to prepare food maple water becomes a restorative beverage  maple sugar using iron pots brought from france europeans and first nations discover how to make maple sugar from the sap already in use by first nations  maple candies king louis xiv craved sweets agathe de repentigny a montréal businesswoman sent him some made of maple sugar in  she exported  pounds of maple sugar to france  bannock first nations and the famed québeccoureurs des bois eat the staple food of bannock a type of bread made of corn flour bear fat and maple sugar to nourish them on their long journeys  sugar shacks the first sugar shacks are made of wood planks in the midth century as of  “sugar parties” are being organized they remain an annual tradition in québec culture  the evaporator the evaporator is patented in the usa and applied to maple syrup production in québec by the small brothers it gradually replaces the iron kettle and increases quality and quantity  canning  ml cans of maple syrup make their appearance on supermarket shelves bringing a major change the consumption of maple sugar is replaced with that of maple syrup  quebecol researchers identify the presence of a molecule quebecol in maple syrup that is found nowhere else in nature quebecol belongs to the polyphenol family molecules beneficial to human health  napsicertifiedmaple water québec maple water enters the market with quality guaranteed by the new napsi certification  the international standard for maple today maple products from québec are exported to more than  countries québec provides  of world production back next video of wxfykjmux watch the videolocate quebec from the forest maple products from québec come from a single ingredient the sap of maple trees the flow of sap is a natural phenomenon unique to north america it occurs each spring when daytime and nighttime temperatures alternate above and below freezing québec maple producers collect the sap and take it to the sugar shack for evaporation and processing into maple products it’s a complex process that demands knowledge and precision   in summertime maple trees produce sugar through photosynthesis sugar allows the trees’ cells to breathe promotes growth and accumulates starch in the roots in the spring the alternating freezethaw cycle between night and day promotes the flow of maple sap at night the cold freezes the tree’s branches causing the gasses in their fibres to contract the sap also freezes but contrary to the gas it expands in the tree fibres all night the water absorbed by the roots rises up through the trunk and as it does so distributes the sugar reserves when the sun comes up the temperature rises and the tree branches thaw the daytime warmth returns the sap to liquid state and the gas in the tree fibres expands again this creates pressure and the sugary sap is pushed through the trunk and this is how sap flows through the maple tree   traditionally maple sap in québec was collected in pails hung on the trees the maple producer would pour the maple water that dripped out into larger containers and drive them back to the sugar shack it’s a lot different today for the most part maple water is gathered through a system of tubing attached to the trees by small nicks the tubes connect to larger conveyance tubes that carry the maple water by gravity or pumping to the sugar shack the maple water comes to huge stainless steel containers and sent to a reverse osmosis unit or directly to the evaporator before being set to boil and become maple syrup it takes an average of  litres of maple water to make  litre of syrup reverse osmosis ro is a technology that concentrates sugar in the sap helping to increase it for example from  to  this step reduces heating costs and the environmental impact of boiling maple water becomes maple syrup when it reaches  degrees brix or a sugar concentration level of  bulk maple syrup is sold by the barrel and subject to québec’s quality control regimen   the sap flows harvest and evaporation video of etxblzfcba maple products there are  pure maple products from québec for everyone allnatural locallyproduced and with numerous health benefits maple is an easy and favourable substitute for other sweeteners increasingly popular as an ingredient maple deserves to be explored in its surprising variety of textures that lends itself to all sorts of combinations the many maple products from québec guaranteed for quality and authenticity are available all year round in a wide variety of formats  maple syrup see voir maple sugar see voir hard maple sugar see voir maple flakes see voir maple butter see voir maple taffy see voir napsicertified maple water see voir maple spirits see voir specialty products see voir maple syrup from québec maple syrup from québec is produced and sold in several colour classes our maple syrup varies in colour and flavour in a completely natural way directly related to the time at which it is harvested in the sugaringoff season early on the syrup is usually clear with a slightly sweet taste golden delicate taste and amber rich taste as the season progresses the syrup becomes darker and more caramelized dark robust taste and very dark strong taste maple syrup from québec contains more than a hundred bioactive compounds and significant quantities of vitamins and minerals golden delicate taste this syrup comes from maple sap harvested at the very beginning of the sugaringoff season it’s distinguished by its light golden hue and sweet delicate flavour it’s a delicious topping for yogourt and ice cream amber rich taste this syrup has a pure rich taste and a magnificent amber colouring it’s ideal as an ingredient in vinaigrettes and all sorts of dishes and desserts dark robust taste this syrup with its more pronounced caramelized flavour is wellsuited for cooking baking and sauces it’s celebrated for the way it enhances the taste of fruity dishes very dark strong taste this syrup is the product of maple sap harvested at the end of the sugaringoff season its flavour more pronounced than any of the previouslylisted syrups is rich and distinctive it colours and perfumes sauces and glazes to perfection maple sugar from québec granulated maple sugar from québec can have the texture of table sugar icing sugar or fructose it’s also found in the form of nuggets this unique product can be used in equal quantities as a substitute wherever recipes call for white or brown sugar the distinctive yet delicate flavour of maple sugar from québec works beautifully in sweets pastries and fruit desserts for example as well as in savoury dishes or in tea and coffee hard maple sugar for grating from québec in compact block form hard maple sugar from québec was highly prized in years past when it was known as country sugar home sugar or sap sugar as it is today…true connaisseurs love it as a garnish grated on french toast toast and pancakes some also put a light dusting of maple sugar on desserts or even meat and poultry dishes adding the subtle taste of maple from québec maple flakes from québec maple flakes from québec are made of freezedried dehydrated maple syrup maple flakes enhance the taste of cocktails meat dishes vegetables and desserts they’re also perfect in crumb coatings and spice mixtures maple flakes from québec are available plain or flavoured maple butter from québec don’t let the name mislead you the everpopular maple butter contains no butter or dairy it’s actually a fondant a pastry term which refers to the buttery texture achieved in its preparation of cooking and churning like all  pure maple products from québec maple butter is made of one sole ingredient maple sap it’s perfect for topping desserts pancakes and french toast adding flavour to custard or making marzipan with almonds maple butter is also a successful addition to aromatic preparations such as pesto and pistou maple taffy from québec maple taffy from québec is made of maple syrup boiled down to a concentrate at sugaringoff time a centuryold tradition in québec hot taffy is poured onto snow to cool and be enjoyed as with all maple products from québec taffy is available all year round in containers large and small aside from heating and pouring it on the snow this product should be tried in desserts like italian meringue and pralines maple taffy from québec can also be used to flavour or enhance the taste of salty foods like stuffed red meat and poultry napsicertified maple water from québec napsicertified maple water is the new rage and will be for years to come both commercially and gastronomically there should be no surprise that maple water from québec is enjoying tremendous popularity it holds  nutritional compounds essential to life growth and protection for the tree it’s a veritable bioactive cocktail with numerous vitamins and minerals organic acids polyphenols and phytohormones the best part is that it contains only  grams of carbohydrates or  calories per  ml napsicertified maple water from québec is first and foremost a pleasure to drink its sweet delicate flavour is quite refreshing athletes especially appreciate its hydrating and regenerative properties its refined taste subtle aroma and light sweetness have caught the attention of cooks and bakers at home and in professional kitchens it has even been noted that maple water creates osmosis that provides the treasured concentration of flavours that brings the fifth savory taste known as “umami”   napsi certification maple water from québec has its own quality certification called napsi established by the federation of québec maple syrup producers for the sake of authenticity and quality the harvesting and processing of napsicertified products must meet rigorous standards that ensure food safety whether by the importer manufacturer packager or chef this seal also guarantees that consumers experience the drinking of fresh crystalline maple water just as it came out of the tree napsi is an acronym that best describes the qualities of maple water from québec natural as it comes from maple treesauthentic as it is the water that nature brings forth from the treepure as there are no added agents or ingredientssterile as it contains no microorganismsintegral as it is whole unrefined with all the compounds that nature gave it for more information go to napsica maple spirits from québec fermented maple water or mapleflavoured and blended liqueur the many types of maple spirits from québec are made to sip or include in your recipes the choice is yours from dessert wine to whisky liqueur cream to sparkling…the possibilities are as endless as the creativity of their artisans and your spirit of adventure maple spirits from québec are pure joy to discover and explore specialty maple products from québec there’s a wealth of local specialty products flavoured with québec maple vinaigrettes vinegars mustards and jellies these products are good to go as is or as accompaniments to savory or sweet dishes the delicate flavour of maple marries particularly well with marinades gourmet salads terrines and the finest cheeses it’s a family of excellent products to discover and add your personal touch to a meal for instance in a unique tapas menu classification guidelines the new government regulations for the classification of maple syrup are now in effect this new grading regime separates maple syrup into two categories and four colour classes as of december   maple products for export are labelled in accordance with the new classification system containers of maple syrup for sale in québec however may display grading by the old or new regulations maple producers who sell only in québec have until december  to change the labelling of their products to reflect the new classification systemgrade a  grade a maple syrup is obtained only by concentrating maple sap does not ferment is clear and uniform in colour is free of objectionable odor or taste and has a maple flavour characteristic of its colour classprocessing grade processing grade maple syrup is obtained only by concentrating maple sap ut it does not qualify for grade a      classification maple products    pdf certifications maple products  special certifications there are a number of different certifications for maple products from québec each attesting to a particular mode of production and all affirming their superior quality  organic certification since maple products from québec are allnatural and locallyproduced you may well ask what the difference is between organicallycertified maple syrup and “classic” maple syrup they’re both made in the same fashion  pure québec maple syrup is produced by boiling the maple water containing about  sugar until it reaches  degrees brix at this density the maple syrup is stable and resistant to alteration the differences between classic and organic syrup actually reside in the way the sap is collected and the product is managed this involves maintenance of the maple stand the biodiversity requirements cleaning products for the equipment auxiliary technology and the proper type of storage containers some of these practices have also been adopted by classic syrup producers so they often overlap with those required by organic producers in québec as elsewhere for a product to be certified “organic” a maple syrup producer must complete a certification process usually administered by a province or state a federal government agency or an organization so mandated by the government producers accept the responsibility to keep records on an ongoing basis and to undergo periodic inspections that verify their compliance most organic certifications forbid the use of nonapproved cleaning and disinfection products among other things practices must also be undertaken to protect the health of maple stands including a limited number of taps per tree the producer working organically observes standards that ensure the entire process and all practices related to the health of the sugar bush are designed to improve product quality and environmental sustainability producers with organic certification commit to respect these requirements ensuring that consumers who choose to buy organic food are getting what they want it bears noting that canadian regulations on organic production are amongst the most stringent in the world kosher certification maple products from québec that are certified kosher meet the requirements of jewish dietary law all production steps and all equipment used are inspected by a rabbi who ensures that every element that comes into contact with the maple products are also certified as kosher this includes the equipment the cleaners used to wash it and the various additives that stabilize the foam at the time of boiling napsicertified maple water napsi is a certification for maple water it was established by the federation of québec maple syrup producers in  after several years of research this certification guarantees a taste experience that’s like a drink freshlydrawn from the maple tree québec’s own napsi certification ensures a clear translucent appearance with freshness and beneficial properties longprovided by the maple tree…as represented by the napsi acronym natural authentic pure sterile integral • harvest of maple water from the forest and storage • transport of maple water from site to processing plant • stabilization of maple water • bottling of maple water • authentication of finished product   for more information on maple water and napsi certification go to napsica other certifications some processors hold quality certifications such as sqf brc food and fssc   find out more in the products and suppliers sections organic kosher napsi other health benefits maple and your health more and more people are making healthy choices a trend which is only bound to get stronger in addition to being  natural with no artificial colouring or flavours maple products from québec are full of vitamins and minerals they also possess antioxidants at a level comparable to many fruits and vegetables no wonder the natural properties and components of maple products are at the heart of research work in québec and abroad the federation of québec maple syrup producers does not encourage increased consumption of sugar used in moderation pure maple products are an attractive option when compared to other natural sweeteners      nutritional value that packs a punch all sugars are not equal maple products from québec contain more vitamins and minerals than honey agave syrup and white sugar a  ml  cup portion of maple syrup satisfies more than  of the recommended daily dosage of manganese  of riboflavin  of zinc  of magnesium and  of calcium and potassium download the nutritional facts    pdf   antioxidant warriors  pure maple products from québec also contain  different antioxidants nine of which are unique to them these polyphenols trace elements and vitamins position maple products amongst fruits and vegetables for nutritional value for example the antioxidant efficacy of maple products is comparable to that of tomatoes broccoli and bananas a  ml  cup serving of syrup depending on its colour supplies from  to  of the recommended daily dosage of antioxidants take note that the darker the maple syrup the more power it packs as an antioxidant download the nutritional facts    pdf   a competitive glycemic index the glycemic index of maple products from québec is equivalent to that of agave syrup corn syrup honey and kuromitsu studies however reveal great variability in the value of the glycemic index from person to person nutritional value that packs a punch antioxidant warriors a competitive glycemic index sports nutrition a true champion maple and sports nutrition maple is not only for the pleasures of the table maple products from québec are the winner’s choice before during and after training professional and amateur athletes are pushing their limits to new levels with this superiorquality allnatural source of energy   why maple products from québec  they are quickly metabolized maple products provide simple carbohydrates that easily metabolize glucose acting as fuel during exercise  they are antioxidants maple products contain  antioxidant compounds a  ml ¼ cup portion of maple syrup stimulates as much antioxidant activity as a tomato or raw broccoli antioxidants protect cells against oxidative stress caused by the free radicals produced during intense exercise  they’re rich in electrolytes maple products contain potassium an electrolyte that helps balance fluids and maintain normal muscle function the more physical your workout the more you need to replace the electrolytes lost due to heavy perspiration  they’re ideal for long training sessions maple products can contribute to increased strength by providing an immediate source of energy to keep up the pace  they promote muscle recovery maple products are an excellent source of manganese and zinc minerals vital to muscle recovery a  ml ¼ cup portion of maple syrup fills  of the daily need for manganese and  of the recommended daily dosage of zinc maple products are richer than other sugars in manganese and zinc  they rebuild your reserves after training maple products help the body recuperate and renew its glycogen reserves   napsicertified maple water hydrate naturally with this exceptional product  napsicertified maple water from québec is another locallyproduced specialty it contains  nutrients including several vitamins and minerals and only  grams of carbohydrates or  calories per  ml serving hydrating and regenerating and so refreshing during or after physical activity it can be taken on its own or mixed with an energy drink athletes love its slightly sweet and delicate flavour to learn more about maple water and the napsi certification please visit napsica why maple products from québec napsicertified maple water hydrate naturally with this exceptional product the secret ingredient maple from our forest to your table while maple products from québec are becoming more and more known for their health benefits chefs and foodlovers are falling for their unique flavour their sweet and incomparable taste and scent improves whatever dish it graces did you know that maple products from québec even stimulate umami the “fifth taste” whose discovery has revolutionized the culinary world   maple and umami umami is one of the five basic tastes along with salty sweet bitter and sour in contrast to the other tastes umami meaning pleasant savory taste in japanese is more complex to describe and understand one theory says maillard reactions cause perception of the umami taste these are chemical reactions that occur between amino acids and sugar when food is being cooked they’re the direct cause of browning and flavour formation after cooking maple products are made by the heating of maple sap maillard reactions can therefore be traced back to this process where umami occurs with maple’s aromatic compounds this is why maple products from québec enhance the flavours of other foods and are now found on the world’s finest tables maple’s complex aromas give chefs the ability to create dishes with new and original tastes surprisingly perhaps maple products from québec are chemically compatible with several essential ingredients found in japanese cuisine for example food cooked with maple syrup mirin and soy sauce has a decidedly enriched flavour other maillard reactions occur when maple sugar reacts with the amino acids of mirin and soy a striking example of umami in action maple and umami fact sheets find technical and commercial fact sheets from maple products from québec online as follows maple syrup    pdf maple water in bulk    pdf maple water in small containers    pdf nutritional value of maple syrup    pdf antioxidant value of maple syrup    pdf economy of quebec  wikipedia economy of quebec from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search this article needs additional citations for verification please help improve this article by adding citations to reliable sources unsourced material may be challenged and removed may  learn how and when to remove this template message economy of quebec  currency canadian dollar cad fiscal year april  to march  trade organisations nafta oecd statistics gdp us  billion  gdp per capita us   population below poverty line facts about economy unemployment    external export