f its territory the first protected area was the creation of mt royal park in  followed by the monttremblant national park in  the quebec government has been working to introduce the electric car since  including contributing financing for technologies such as the tm mфtive an electric motor designed and manufactured in quebec hydroquébec has recently tested more than  imiev in order to gradually introduce the charging stations across the province this is the largest pilot test of electric cars in canada quebec was the first province in canada to allow the zenn car to drive on the roads during the inaugural speech of  jean charest announced five priorities for the next  years including the plan nord and called for a revolution in electric cars on november   premier jean charest announced targets for reducing greenhouse gases during the united nations climate change conference in copenhagen quebec will cut its emissions by  by the year  compared to international reference of  on january   a new law came into force to reduce greenhouse gases from automobiles which represent  of quebec ghgs this new law stipulates that car manufacturers serving the territory of quebec must meet an emission ceiling of  grams of ghgkm or approximatively  l km this level must be reduced annually up to  grams of ghgkm or approximatively  l km in  these standards are as stringent as those in california united states according to the government of quebec the provincial government plans to offer up to  rebate towards the purchase of an electric car the government hopes that by  a quarter of cars purchased in quebec will be electric the plan would position quebec as a world leader in electrified transportation according to jean charest tata indica ev engine bay featuring tm mфtive electric motor quebec became the first region in north america to set a carbon tax since  consumers pay a special tax on gasoline since july  quebec has imposed a carbon tax that affect more than  of industries in the province this tax will be mandatory from  the sectors affected by this carbon tax will have to reduce their carbon dioxide below   kilotonnes per year only the forest industry agriculture and waste industries are not affected by this tax in addition the quebec government plans to recover  of putrescible organic matter by  in order to reduce its emissions quebec climate policy has been harshly criticised by the federal government under prime minister stephen harper in  former minister jim prentice has openly criticized quebecs plan to set ghg standards for motor vehicles sold in the province describing it as lunatic however ten months later prentice successor john baird has praised quebec as a world leader in ghg abatement most productive sectorsedit aerospaceedit there are some  companies of the aerospace sector that employ  people it includes aerospace companies such as airplane manufacturer bombardier jet engine companies pratt  whitney and rollsroyce canada flight simulator builder cae defence contractor lockheed martin and l communications and helicopter manufacturer bell helicopter  various international organisations have established their headquarters in quebec notably the international air transport association and the international civil aviation organization financeedit the finance insurance real estate and leasing industry employs  people including the largest money manager in canada caisse de dépôt et placement du québec transportationedit quebecs ground transportation industry generated  billion in revenue at the beginning of  it employs some  people and includes major original equipment manufacturers such as bombardier paccar novabus prévost car komatsu international and many suppliers and subcontractors quebec has eight deepwater ports for merchandise shipping and in   million tons of merchandise was carried by  cargo ships through the saint lawrence seaway the income created by this traffic is over  million per annum the port of montreal is the sec