nd tangy in québec we are as fond of them as we are of our traditions despite the temptation to eat them all straight from the farm québec is a leading supplier of processed products derived from berries ranging from dried sweetened products to concentrates to iqf fruit maple syrup did you know that québec produces more than  percent of the world’s maple syrup this natural nutritious product comes from the sap of the sugar maple tree and is produced through the evaporation of maple water it takes  gallons of maple water to produce  gallon of maple syrup did you know that maple syrup has many flavor profiles generally speaking the lighter the color grade the more delicate the flavor and the darker the color grade the stronger the taste these flavors are heavily influenced by the « terroir » or growing regions of the sugar maple trees and can give maple syrup a range of taste from traditional maple to vanilla or fruity… the possibilities are endless more than just another traditional product maple syrup is one of the cultural food ingredients associated with quebecers from the provinces origins to today  maple syrup remains a star ingredient in québec and international cooking in the st century maple from québec is available in a variety of traditional and innovative forms such as sugars chips whipped creamy maple maple vinegar maple flakes maple pearls and much more buy wine alcohols and spirits instore and online  saqcom accessibility go to content sitemap stores saq inspire contact us français sign up my account  open the sign in window this link opens the sign in form in a new window which offers the close button at the end existing customer email password forgot your password new customer or signed up in store start here if youre new to our website or registered for saq inspire in a saq store complete my registration close close the sign in window press keyboards down arrow to use the submenu products wine spirits champagne and sparkling wine port and fortified w